			<div class="content" id="post-content-3754064">
									

<p>Greetings Skippers.</p>
<p>As pointed out in <a href="http://05command.wikidot.com/forum/t-5494797/project-foundation:project-plan">my project plan</a> the next task to accomplish is the gathering of resources.</p>
<p>In order to do that, we're posting a series of threads to figure out who we have available to use, resource wise, and what skills they possess.</p>
<p>Some disclaimers before you post:</p>
<ol>
<li>All work done for Project Foundation is on a <strong>volunteer</strong> basis, and you should not expect, and are not entitled to, compensation of any kind.</li>
<li>Completing work for Project Foundation does not entitle you to any Staff Role or authority on the wiki, or any eventual platform.</li>
<li>If you volunteer your skills you accept that you will most likely have to work under a manager who will assign you tasks to perform. You are free to make suggestions to your manager; however at the end of the day, they will likely have the final say on the direction of your work.</li>
<li>Working for Project Foundation will require a minimum commitment to producing work within a reasonable timeframe as assigned by the project manager, or your manager. Your manager will work with your schedule but ultimately decides expectations on task completion dates.</li>
<li>Any art work produced for PF will have to be licensed as part of the Site. You're probably going to just let us use it with credit to you as the artist.</li>
</ol>
<p>All of that being said, this post is a call for: Artists.</p>
<p>We are looking for people who can hit the ground running with this area, and be able to perform the required tasks without significant instruction or hand-holding.</p>
<p>If you feel you have these skills, and would like to collaborate on Project Foundation, please respond below with the following responses:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Username</strong>: &lt;Your Wiki Username&gt;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Please give me a link to your DeviantArt, or your tumblr, wheverever:</strong></li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p><strong>FAQ</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">FAQ</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Q. Magnus, I have this other skill that I can&#8230;</strong><br />
A. Cool, post in the relevant thread.</p>
<p><strong>Q. So how will I know I'm on the team?</strong><br />
A. If the management team feels your skills are applicable, we'll put your name on a big ol' spreadsheet of skills and talents. You'll get a wiki PM from someone on the team to coordinate.</p>
<p><strong>Q. Awesome, when do I get work to do?</strong><br />
A. Eventually. We need to figure out what exactly needs to get done, before anything can get done.</p>
<p><strong>Q. I drew this kickass darkblade once, and it had like katanas and&#8230;</strong><br />
A. We're looking for people who are going to be able to create assets for our site. Logos, backgrounds, etc. If you're making fan art, kick ass, you do you. This is a little different.</p>
<p><strong>Q. So&#8230;what, you're just asking if Zhange or Sunny is willing to help?</strong><br />
A. No. Lots of people who make digital assets are proficient in graphic design rather than traditional &quot;art&quot;. (Though I would love to have Zhange or Sunny on the teeeeam &lt;3 :D)</p>
</div>
</div>
