<p><strong>User</strong><br />
<span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cortz" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3933857); return false;">cortz</a></span></p>
<p><strong>About</strong><br />
A senior design student working towards<br />
a BFA in Graphic Design at an art college.<br />
My focus is in digital product design, with<br />
proficiency in brand/identity design and<br />
creative art direction.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I don't necessarily have any professional<br />
working experience to back that up, but<br />
I've worked on a few sponsored projects<br />
in both small and large teams. I will be<br />
at an internship this summer, working<br />
as an interactive design intern.</p>
<p><strong>Why</strong><br />
I'm a stranger, but I really admire the<br />
works and the community here, and with<br />
such a huge repository to organize, I find it<br />
to be a very interesting challenge to tackle.<br />
Frankly, I'm not here to simply make &quot;logos&quot;<br />
and &quot;digital assets&quot;. Rather, I'm interested<br />
in helping craft and redefine the entire exp-<br />
erience from concept to production.</p>
<p><strong>Work</strong><br />
My portfolio is only available for private<br />
viewing at this time. However I've included<br />
a sample of a conceptual re-brand project<br />
that I've done in the past.</p>
<p><a href="https://imgur.com/a/rKD1xyR">Sample Project</a></p>
<p><strong>Closing</strong><br />
I may be overstepping as someone who has<br />
just came in, but from reading through the<br />
project plan, I noticed a weakness in know-<br />
ledge from a design perspective, and so I<br />
hope to be able to help with that.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
